Adding bug management tool for BMO exports

This genmd.py script serves as glue between bugzilla CSV exports and
advisory markdown files. It can amend existing advisories with new
"fixed_in" header entries and generate .md skeletons for new advisories.

It also contains an .md parser that can spot bugs in advisories and
extractis bug-to-mfsa mapping.

Adding Firefox OS 2.2 advisories

This adds MFSA-72 to -77, covering bugs exclusively fixed in Firefox OS.

Fixing comment anchor deleted by accident
Fixing the duplication in advisory title

Fixing broken HTML

My parser would choke on few advisories that contained obviously
broken HTML, like missing and duplicate closing tags.

Removing "fixed_in:" header field

mfsa2007-10 was the only one to ever use the fixed_in header field,
and because of its redundancy with the announced field, I'm removing
it from the header.

Renaming "affects" header field to "vulnerable"

mfsa2006-30 is the only advisory to ever use the "affects" header
field, so I'm renaming it to "vulnerable" which was used a few times
during 2005.

Fixing linebreak in header

I'm removing this linebreak inside the "title:" header field of
mfsa2005-57, because it is the only one and special handling in the
header parser would add disproportional complexity.

Fixing broken Bugzilla URLs containing '
'

A number of advisories contained broken bugzilla links where one
or more bug IDs were prefixed by '
', effectively masking them
in the resulting buglist. This was probably the result of a broken
line feed conversion.
